2026-03-28T09:48:15.963Z JOY-007D item.created "AI instructions use JOY_AUTHOR env var instead of --author flag" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T09:48:22.946Z JOY-007D comment.added "AI agents currently prefix joy commands with JOY_AUTHOR env var (e.g. JOY_AUTHOR="ai:claude@joy" joy close ...). This breaks the shell permission model because the allowed command is "joy", not "JOY_AUTHOR=... joy". Fix: update AI instructions and skill to use --author flag instead (e.g. joy close JOY-0005 --author ai:claude@joy)." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T09:48:24.334Z JOY-006A comment.added "Note: until this item is implemented, AI agents must use --author flag instead of JOY_AUTHOR env var. Using the env var breaks shell permission matching for the joy command. See JOY-007D." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T10:05:32.675Z JOY-0004 comment.added "Closing as wontfix. The acronym is already read-only in project set, preventing accidental changes. If someone manually edits project.yaml, mixed ID prefixes (old and new) coexist without issues -- item lookup is ID-based, not acronym-based. New items get the new prefix, old items keep theirs, and all references (parent, deps) continue to work. The only downside is cosmetic inconsistency, which does not justify the complexity of a full migration (renaming files, rewriting all ID references, updating event log)." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
